data.enText: a group or collection of things or people, often one that is large or impressive

data.chText: 一大批形状大小不一的瓶子
data.enText: a vast array of bottles of different shapes and sizes
a way of organizing and storing related data in a computer memory
a set of numbers, signs or values arranged in rows and columns
to arrange a group of things in a pleasing way so that they are in order

data.chText: 在搁架上整齐地排列着大大小小各式各样的罐子。
data.enText: Jars of all shapes and sizes were arrayed on the shelves.
to arrange soldiers in a position from which they are ready to attack

tr: an arrangement of aerials spaced to give desired directional characteristics

example: it was a bewildering array of books
his tools were in an orderly array on the basement wall
an array of troops in battle order

tr: align oneself with a group or a way of thinking
lay out orderly or logically in a line or as if in a line

value.def: An array of different things or people is a large number or wide range of them.

example.ex: As the deadline approached she experienced a bewildering array of emotions...
example.tran: 随着最后期限的临近，她开始心绪纷乱，不知所措。

example.ex: A dazzling array of celebrities are expected at the Mayfair gallery to see the pictures.
example.tran: 梅费尔美术馆期待星光璀璨的各界名流来欣赏这些画。

value.def: An array of objects is a collection of them that is displayed or arranged in a particular way.

example.ex: There was an impressive array of pill bottles stacked on top of the fridge...
example.tran: 冰箱上显眼地摆放着许多药瓶。

example.ex: We visited the local markets and saw wonderful arrays of fruit and vegetables.
example.tran: 我们去了当地的市场，看见了一排排摆放整齐的水果和蔬菜。

value.def: An array of instruments such as telescopes or solar panels is a number of them that are connected together to form a single unit.

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft adj N, N <l>of</l> n

value.tran: （多个望远镜、太阳能电池板之类的仪器设备连接在一起构成的）阵列

value.def: In science and mathematics, an array of things such as atoms or numbers is a regular pattern or structure that is formed by them.

example.ex: ...methods which can be used to create an ordered array of molecules within materials...
example.tran: 能使材料内部的分子有序排列的方法

example.ex: The image is then stored on the computer hard disk as a vast array of black or white dots.
example.tran: 这幅图像当时就以大量黑点或白点排列的形式被存入电脑硬盘。
